\f1\b \cf2 Academic Eligibility:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b0 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Candidates should have scored min. of 70% or 7 CGPA (Without Rounding-up) in SSC/10th, HSC/12th /Diploma (in case done) and B. Tech\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Eligible Courses- B. Tech (Computer Science / IT / E&TC)\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Candidates should be completing the eligible course in 2024 without any backlog and should have Consolidated mark sheet or Provisional Degree Certificate issued at the time of offer.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
There should not be a gap of more than one year after completing SSC and before joining the graduate/post-graduate course. Also, there should not be a loss of academic year after joining a course.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Note- Rounding up of marks to 70% to become eligible for the registration is NOT valid.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Selection Process
\f0\b0 : Candidates will have to undergo the tests below, each acting as a filter for the next stage of the selection process.\cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Aptitude Test, English Essay/Story.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Technical & Psychometric Test\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Verbal Communication Test\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Technical Interview\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
HR Interview\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The first 2 rounds may be conducted in College Premises through Pool-campus Mode and further rounds from Verbal Communication test till HR Interview will be done through virtual mode. We will keep you posted accordingly.\cf0 \
\
\cf2 Eligible candidates will be receiving All rounds test links from us on their registered email ID. Please ask the candidates to check Junk/Spam mail as well.\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

